summary: 2001 REXALL ANTHEM MOTORHOME TRANSMISSION. THE MOTOR HOME WAS BUILT TO LOW AND WHEN IT WAS RAISED IT THREW THE DRIVE LINE OUT OF ALIGNMENT WHICH CAUSED THE TRANSMISSION AND REAR END TO FAIL.  THE DRIVERS SIDE FRONT TIRE RUBBED AGAINST THE WHEEL WELL AND THE WHEEL CAME AWAY FROM THE BODY. *JB
